7 PROPOSED COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; creating an
income tax credit for certain eligible business
9 entities for credit card processing fees paid in
excess of certain amount; defining terms; providing
10 for allocation; prohibiting the credit from reducing
the income tax liability of the eligible business
11 entity to less than zero; providing carryover;
providing for codification; and providing an
12 effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2357.701 of Title 68, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. As used in this section:
20 1. "Credit card processing fee" means the total percentage rate
21 charged by a payment processor, acquirer, or similar financial
22 institution to a business for the processing of credit card or debit
23 card transactions; and
24
Req. No. 15971 Page 1

1 2. "Eligible business entity" means a general partnership,
2 limited partnership, limited liability partnership, limited
3 liability limited partnership, limited liability company,
4 corporation, trust, estate or any other lawfully recognized entity
5 which accepts payment for goods or services by means of a credit
6 card or debit card.
7 B. For taxable years beginning on or after January 1, 2027,
8 there shall be allowed as a credit against the tax imposed pursuant
9 to Section 2355 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes equal to one
10 hundred percent (100%) of the portion of the eligible business
11 entity's credit card processing fees that exceeds two percent (2%)
12 of the gross amount of all credit card or debit card transactions
13 processed during the taxable year.
14 C. The credit authorized pursuant to the provisions of this
15 section shall be allocable to the partners, shareholders, members,
16 or other equity owners of an eligible business entity that is
17 authorized to be treated as a partnership for purposes of federal
18 income tax reporting for the taxable year for which the tax credit
19 authorized by this section is claimed on the applicable return,
20 together with required schedules, forms, or reports of the partners,
21 shareholders, members, or other equity owners of the eligible
22 business entity.
23
24
Req. No. 15971 Page 2

1 D. The credit authorized by this section shall not be used to
2 reduce the income tax liability of the eligible business entity to
3 less than zero (0).
4 E. To the extent not used, the credit authorized by this
5 section shall be allowed to carry over, in order, to each of the
6 five (5) following taxable years.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective January 1, 2027.
